Preparatory Committee of Macao SAR to Be Set UP Soon: Qian 
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said here today that the
Preparatory Committee of the Macao Special Administrative Region will
be established very soon.
Qian made the remark at a press conference at the First Session of the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) this morning.
"The day of Macao's return to the motherland is drawing near. We are
very pleased to see that the preparations for that are proceeding
smoothly during the transitional period in Macao, and China and
Portugal have also had an exchange of high-level visits," he said.
With regard to the specific preparations, a preparatory committee for
the establishment of the Macao Special Administrative Region will soon
be formed, and this falls under the authority of the National People's
Congress.
"I think the committee will soon be established," Qian said.
